<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Gets the number of positions a character is likely to occupy when output</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><Highlight kind="comment">/// on a terminal (&quot;character width&quot;). This depends on the implementation of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><Highlight kind="comment">/// terminal, and there&#39;s no standard definition of character width.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The implementation defines it in a way that is expected to be compatible</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><Highlight kind="comment">/// with a generic Unicode-capable terminal.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\return Character width:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#42; ErrorNonPrintableCharacter (-1) for non-printable characters (as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><Highlight kind="comment">///     identified by isPrintable);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#42; 0 for non-spacing and enclosing combining marks;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#42; 2 for CJK characters excluding halfwidth forms;</Highlight></CodeLine>
